  "prompt": "Is it wise for someone to opt for UWaterloo instead of Georgia Tech for an undergrad program (computer engineering)?",
  "response": "Both the University of Waterloo (UWaterloo) and Georgia Tech are highly respected institutions for computer engineering. The best choice depends on individual preferences and goals. Here are some considerations:\n\nUWaterloo Advantages:\n- World-renowned co-op program\n- Strong reputation in computer engineering\n- Located in Canada with potential immigration pathways\n- Lower international tuition compared to US schools\n- Excellent tech ecosystem in Ontario\n- Strong research opportunities\n\nGeorgia Tech Advantages:\n- Top-ranked US engineering school\n- Larger research facilities\n- Strong industry connections in the US\n- More diverse campus environment\n- Potentially better scholarship opportunities\n- Located in Atlanta, a major tech hub\n\nFactors to consider:\n1. Career goals (US vs. Canadian job market)\n2. Total cost of education\n3. Personal preference for location\n4. Specific program details\n5. Visa/immigration considerations\n\nRecommendation:\n- If you prefer North American tech opportunities and want a robust co-op program, UWaterloo is excellent\n- If you're more focused on US tech scene and want a prestigious US engineering degree, Georgia Tech might be better\n\nUltimately, both are outstanding choices. The \"best\" option depends on your individual circumstances, career aspirations, and personal preferences.",
